Speaker of the Imo State House of Assembly, Dr Chiji Collins and seven lawmakers have defected to the All Progressives Congress (APC). The other lawmakers are Hon Uche Ogbuagu (Ikeduru); Hon Dominic Ezerioha (Oru West);  Hon Chigozie Nwaneri (Oru East); Hon Kanayo Onyemaechi (Owerri West); Kennedy Ibe (Obowo); Onyemaechi Njoku (Ihitte/Uboma), and Eddy Obinna (Aboh Mbaise). Dr Collins announced their defection from the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) during plenary on Tuesday. As it stands now, APC now has 18 lawmakers and will produce the new Deputy Speaker, while while PDP has eight. Just on Monday, the State chairman of PDP, Chief Charles Ezekwem announced his resignation from the position and party. Following the ouster of former Governor, Rt Hon Emeka Ihedioha by the Supreme Court two weeks ago, politicians started leaving PDP in droves for the APC. Meanwhile, Governor Hope Uzodinma is expected to send the list of his proposed cabinet to the Assembly soon.